Iran has no expansionist ambitions - commander . Iran has no expansionist ambitions but could counter any aggression against its territory , a senior Iranian military officer said in remarks published on Saturday . Brigadier Rahim Ebrahimi , deputy commander of ground forces for intelligence and operations , told the English - language Tehran Times the Islamic republic ' s forces , with their experience in the 1980 - 88 Iran - Iraq war , could crack down on any aggression against Iranian territory . They were ready to enter the scene , whenever and wherever there was possible aggression against Iran , upon the permission of Iran ' s supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei . Commenting on the U . S . military presence in the Gulf and its action against Iraq , Ebrahimi said Washington was pursuing nothing but its own interests . 
